    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-08-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-08-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="254" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d254">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                de Stoeckl</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-08-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 3, 1868.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to transmit herewith for
                            your information, and that of the government which you represent, a copy
                            of an instruction <pb facs="0535" n="487" xml:id="pg_487"/> which, on
                            the 14th of July, was addressed by this department to the United States
                            minister at Yeddo.<note n="*" xml:id="d254fn1">For this inclosure, see
                                correspondence with Japan.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Accept, sir, a renewed assurance of my very high consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward de Stoeckl</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
